title.narrative: Central healthcare supply chain set up and procurement charges

description.narrative: This activity (Central healthcare supply chain set up and procurement charges) is a component of Ebola Central Health Care Supply Chain Platform reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £10,632,197. This component benefits Sierra Leone, and works in the following sector(s): Material relief assistance and services , Relief co-ordination and support services. , with the following implementing partners: International Procurement Agency. The start date is 15-12-2014 and the end date is 31-03-2016.
